The paper discusses resource allocation and sharing in mobile edge computing, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of a cooperative game theory framework further supports the likelihood of cs.GT as a relevant sub-category. The paper also involves optimization (cs.DC) and multi-objective decision making, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
